"The Beijing Youth Ice Hockey League of Xinhua Full Media+ Ignites Olympic Passion - Xinhua News Network"
On December 11th, Beijing Dreaming Team player Pang Yao Tian (middle) shot a goal in the game.
On that day, the 2021-2022 Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Club League continues to compete in Beijing's major ice rinks.
This season's league is divided into regular season and playoffs, with athletes aged from U6 to U18, divided into competitive and selection groups, attracting nearly 3,600 players from 256 representative teams in the city.
The Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Club League, after more than ten years of development, has now become a platform for Beijing ice hockey enthusiasts to compare techniques and to make many friends, and it is also a channel for sending excellent players to the Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Team and the Young Team.
The league plays a driving role in Beijing's youth ice hockey activities, reigniting Beijingers' passion for ice hockey and laying the foundation for later ice hockey development in Beijing after the Winter Olympics.
